This paper deals with optimizing caching placement and channel allocation in wireless networks, which is a common problem in the field of network optimization. The use of D2D communication and HetNets is also mentioned, which falls under the category of network architecture and protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of caching and content delivery could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
